<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 14 at 10:24AM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Light Snow This Afternoon...
An area of light snow will cross southeast West Virginia this
afternoon. Snowfall amounts will generally be less than one inch.
Up to two inches are possible in western Greenbrier County and
near Flat Top. Temperatures this afternoon will be in the upper
teens to mid 20s.
A west wind at 15 to 30 mph with gusts to 50 mph will produce
wind chills in the single digits and teens.
Use caution when traveling this afternoon. Untreated roads and
sidewalks may be slippery.
More snow is expected Monday and Monday night.</description>
